setColour

public void setColour(java.awt.Color c)
Sets colour for grid lines. By default, major gridlines are drawn at 50% and minor at 30% transparency of this colour. Colour defaults to normal foreground (usually black).

Appropriate colours can be obtained from World.convertColour(String).

Parameters:
c - New colour

setXSpacing

public void setXSpacing(java.lang.String sSpacing)
                 throws GraphFormatException
Sets X spacing of gridlines. You can have major and minor grid lines; minor ones are usually more transparent.

Parameters:
sSpacing - For example "0.5" if you want major gridlines every 0.5, or "0.5,0.1" if you also want minor ones every 0.1.
Throws:
GraphFormatException - If spacing string is invalid

setYSpacing

setOpacity

public void setOpacity(java.lang.String sOpacity)
                throws GraphFormatException
Sets opacity of gridlines. The default is 0.25 for major and half that for minor.

Parameters:
sOpacity - For example "0.5" if you want major gridlines to be 50%, or "0.5,0.1" if you also want minor ones to be 10%. (Minor ones default to half the major one.)
Throws:
GraphFormatException - If opacity string is invalid
